From 866c0680bf0d0978c35d6ff0f30062057b005be4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: t <t@t>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 06:18:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(traits): close T-2/T-3 + skillPickChoice +
 effects-as-labels contract
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the remaining open questions in docs/schema/02-traits.md and
fills the data gaps the owner pointed out during the traits audit.

Apply ORDER: this patch goes AFTER refactor-traits-T1-drop-robot-dups
(which removes legacy robotRules/robotType/robotBodyPlan from data and
the trait.modifiers.robotBodyPlan fallback in code). Patches do not
touch the same lines, but the T-1 patch is the architectural pre-req.

Data (data/traits/traits.json):
  - ncr-infantryman: ncrInfantryWeaponIds → weaponDamageBonus
    [{ weaponIds: [...5...], bonus: 1 }]. Same 5 weapons as before.
  - ncr-good-soul: modifiers were {}. Now carries the contract
    skillPickChoice: { count: 2, from: ['SPEECH','MEDICINE','REPAIR',
    'SCIENCE','BARTER'] } — source of truth for what is currently
    hardcoded as GOOD_SOUL_SKILL_KEYS in CharacterScreen.js.
  - ncr-home-on-the-range, ncr-technique-of-descent, ncr-brahmin-baron,
    survivor-quick-shot: modifiers were {}. Added effects: ['<label_id>']
    so the UI has an anchor to render their localized labels (no
    mechanical effect, per owner). The label ids are intentionally
    *_label-suffixed to make the UI-only nature explicit.
  - ncr-resident: stays a pure container ({ isMultiTrait, subTraitIds }).
    No self weaponDamageBonus — only chosen sub-traits carry bonuses.

domain/traits.js:
  - getWeaponDamageBonus(source, weapon): sum of matching records
    inside one source. Matches by weaponIds[], weaponId, or skillKey
    (canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE). bonus may be negative.
  - getWeaponDamageBonusFromSources(sources, weapon): additive over
    all active sources (parent trait + sub-traits + future perks/chem).

components/screens/WeaponsAndArmorScreen/WeaponsAndArmorScreen.js:
  - WeaponCard pulls 'trait' from useCharacter().
  - Hardcoded NCR-Infantryman branch replaced by the universal path
    through getWeaponDamageBonusFromSources([parent, ...subTraits]).
    Future perks/chem with weaponDamageBonus will be picked up the
    same way — no further UI changes needed.

domain/weaponDamageBonus.test.js:
  - Removed the assertion that demanded a self-bonus on ncr-resident.
    Per owner: resident is a multi-trait container with no mechanical
    effect of its own. The test was added in commit 5fe99a1 without
    owner approval.

docs/schema/02-traits.md:
  - T-2 marked ✅ (weaponDamageBonus contract + impl).
  - T-3 marked ✅ (canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE everywhere — closed
    earlier by refactor-skills-canonical, just updating status).
  - New §: 'Effects как метки для UI' — explains the contract for
    string-flag labels (vs real mechanics).
  - New §: 'Контракт skillPickChoice' — picker-data field.

docs/schema/06-modifiers.md:
  - skillBonusChoice (the previous draft) replaced by the actual
    field used in data: skillPickChoice { count, from }. Status 🟡
    (data present in ncr-good-soul; picker UI is in 07-trait-debt).

docs/schema/07-trait-debt.md (new):
  - Single source of truth for what is currently a label and needs
    a real implementation later. 7 chapters:
      1. Radiation counter (ghoul healing + child-of-atom charge).
      2. Stealth Boy addiction (shadow).
      3. weaponDifficultyHint (UI warnings: infantryman / technique
         of descent).
      4. UI rules left over from robotRules (no_consumables_food_rest,
         armor whitelists → origin.armorRules).
      5. Real picker UI for skillPickChoice (ncr-good-soul).
      6. Built-in weapons & robot attacks (built_in_laser,
         self_destruct).
      7. Numbers that still need owner input (minuteman effects, etc).

Verified by in-process simulation (no vitest available in sandbox):
20/20 assertions pass — including the data tests on ncr-infantryman,
the explicit absence of a self-bonus on ncr-resident, and the
skillPickChoice shape on ncr-good-soul.
